		<td><b>mp3 players from Japan to England</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi, I'm wondering about running an MP3 player (Sony) bought in Japan on an English version of Windows.  The people at the place where it was being sold told me that it would be fine on a Japanese version of Windows, but that it is Japanese-only, implying that it wouldn't work on an English version of Windows.  This device runs on USB and is charged by the USB port and my thinking is that since it connects to USB there shouldn't be a hardware issue with this, but perhaps there is something in the English version of Windows that prevents it from working?  Perhaps one of y'all might know something about this?  Thanks. ^-^

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
